<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10144c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10144c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10144c"> 144(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font>&apos;s red coat</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Personal remarks in Africa are permissible, and you will perceive that Rob is dressed in his Sunday best for the occasion, to wit, an utterly abominable soldier&apos;s uniform, probably now entering its teens. Fat and fifty, our friend is obviously bursting for relief, for the rag-shop <mark>red coat</mark> is giving him a claret-coloured face. With every button straining at its fastenings, observe how the tight-unto-choking collar makes his oxe-neck overflow in waves of fat. <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 119</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01070b" href="c01all.htm#c01070b">VI.C.01:070(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
